President Biden held a ceremony at the White House to award the Presidential Medal of Freedom, the highest civilian award in the United States, to several individuals who have made significant contributions to society. The recipients included Simone Biles, the most decorated American gymnast in history; Megan Rapinoe, a champion soccer player and advocate for equal pay; Wilma Vaught, a retired Air Force Brigadier General and advocate for women in the military; and Steve Jobs, the late co-founder of Apple who revolutionized the technology industry. Other recipients included civil rights activists, healthcare workers, and leaders in various fields. The President praised each recipient for their accomplishments and their dedication to making a positive impact on the world.